    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Is Smoking Just About Choice?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Don Z Block letter on Mario Vargas Llosa's Sept 1 article holds smokers harm nonsmokers who must inhale secondhand smoke</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Languid Sort of Suicide,'' by Mario Vargas Llosa (Op-Ed, Sept. 1):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Languid Sort of Suicide,'' by Mario Vargas Llosa (Op-Ed, Sept. 1):</p>
        <p>Smokers harm not only themselves but also those who have to inhale secondhand smoke. In places like Spain and Latin America -- but also the United States -- tobacco smoke does not simply ''complicate life'' for the former smoker: it is dangerous for both the former smoker and the nonsmoker.</p>
        <p>DON Z. BLOCK  Malvern, Pa., Sept. 1, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
